<Layout>
    <main>
        <h1>Tianyi Cao</h1>
        <h2>Who I Am</h2>
        <p>
            From China, born in 2000. Currently PhD student in biophysics at LMU
            Munich, researching targeted LNP gene delivery. Grew up in Shanghai
            up to high school, then stayed in Munich for bachelor, master, and
            PhD.
        </p>

        <h2>What I Do</h2>
        <p>
            Vibe coding. I reinvent the wheels I hate to use. Here are some
            projects I like:
        </p>
        <p>Scientific tooling:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/keejkrej/nd2-rs">nd2-rs</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/keejkrej/czi-rs">czi-rs</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/keejkrej/bioformats-zig"
                    >bioformats-zig</a
                >
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/keejkrej/mdat">mdat</a>
            </li>
            <li>
